parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: From pros and echo; to hold the mind towards, i.e. Pay attention to, be cautious about, apply oneself to, adhere to.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
From pseudes and prophetes; a spurious prophet, i.e. Pretended foreteller or religious impostor.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Plural
Verb - Present Indicative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Plural

str2: To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
A sheep. Probably neuter of a presumed derivative of probaino; something that walks forward, i.e., a sheep.
A garment, raiment, clothing. From enduo; apparel.
A primary particle; but, and, etc.
From eso; from inside; also used as equivalent to eso.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Rapacious, ravenous; a robber, an extortioner. From harpazo; rapacious.
A wolf, of perhaps a jackal; often applied to persons of wolfish proclivities. Perhaps akin to the base of leukos; a wolf.
